						               													<description>Bang! Bang! is a two player strategy skirmish game where you go head to head as commanders leading your squad of soldiers onto a battlefield in an attempt to eliminate each other. The only tools at your disposal are the Combat Card, your wits, and the roll of the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is split into three phases. You begin in the Spawn Phase, placing your squad onto the map, choosing carefully where to set them along the orange spawn clicks. Clicks are the spots on the board used to determine movement. Once both players finish the Spawn Phase, you then enter the first Move Phase. Start by taking your units using a limited number of moves out of their spawn while attempting to establish line of sight so you can take shots at the enemy. Both players go through one Move phase without firing shots. After your second Move Phase is finished, you enter the Kill Phase and get to take any shots you have available by rolling the dice. Once your Kill phase is over, the turn goes to your opponent, and he gets to do the same by Moving then Killing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each class of soldier is unique and has an ideal range for engagement. The Sniper and Light Machine Gun are best from a distance, the Shotgun and Sub-Machine Gun are great up close, and the Assault Rifle has a sweet spot in the middle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Combat Card details every soldier's stats, and will show you what you need to roll to land a killshot. After you've taken your shots, any soldiers you hit get the chance to roll for cover, and if they make it, will stay alive and get to keep fighting!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bang! Bang! uses a classic Deathmatch win condition, so the first person to fully eliminate the enemy squad wins. It comes with three maps of varying difficulty, giving players a fresh battle experience as they improve.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
